then recursively sort each of those 3

lets say n = 8

so in prev we have
level 0 -> j=0, n=8, subproblem = 1
level 1 -> j=1, n=8/2, subproblem = 2
level 2 -> j=2, n= ((8/2)/2), subproblem = 4
level 3 -> j=3, n= (((8/2)/2)2), subproblem = 8

butnow we have
level 0 -> j=0, n=8, subproblem = 1
level 1 -> j=1, n=8/3, subproblem = 3
level 2 -> j=2, n= ((8/3)/3), subproblem = 9
level 3 -> j=3, n= (((8/3)/3)3), subproblem = 27

since the merge step takes linear time -> n

total work = merge + sort
total work = work per level * number of levels
total work at level j = number of sumproblem at that level * work per sumproblem
total work single level = 3^j . c . n/3^j = cn

log base 3 division
cn log base 3 . n = n log n

